cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with interactive image search, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The use of natural language to communicate preferences suggests a potential overlap with natural language processing (cs.CL). The learning of ranking functions and iterative updates to relevance functions suggest a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application of the technique to people, products, and scenes suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM).
